Betty Friedan, a pioneer of the feminist movement, passed away at 85 due to heart failure.
Her groundbreaking book, "The Feminine Mystique," challenged societal norms and sparked a revolution for women's rights.
Friedan's legacy lives on through the progress made for women and girls today.
Despite criticism of her past, Friedan's impact on gender equality cannot be denied.
Her work continues to inspire and empower women worldwide.
Friedan's contributions to feminism will forever be remembered as she leaves behind a legacy of courage and determination.
